Manual dishwashing: Wash, rinse, sanitize technique
Ensure manual dishwashing includes the three steps: wash, rinse, and sanitize
Chlorine sanitizer concentration must be at least 100 parts per million at 24°C or greater for at least 45 seconds
Quaternary ammonium compound must be at least 200 parts per million at 24°C or greater for at least 45 seconds
Corrected During Inspection
Food contact surfaces washed / rinsed / sanitized after each use and following any operations when contamination may have occurred
Wash, rinse and sanitize equipment / utensils after each use or as often as necessary
Chlorine sanitizer concentration must be at least 100 parts per million
Quaternary ammonium sanitizer concentration must be at least 200 parts per million
Corrected During Inspection
Food Handler Training Not in Compliance
Thermometers used to verify storage, food preparation, and hot holding temperatures Corrected During Inspection
